1
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:35,940
[Light to the Night]

2
00:01:35,980 --> 00:01:38,980
[Episode 25]

3
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:44,300
That's a pretty airtight story.

4
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:47,130
This whole story

5
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,770
you've been plotting it

6
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:49,930
for years, haven't you?

7
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,070
Xiaohe.

8
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,850
Officer He.

9
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,460
I even admitted

10
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,930
I pushed my own mother

11
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:08,730
off a cliff by accident.

12
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:09,710
I told you that myself.

13
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:10,890
So making up anything else,

14
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:11,940
what would be the point?

15
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,500
How would that help me?

16
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,060
Oh, right.

17
00:02:21,830 --> 00:02:22,530
Officer,

18
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,970
that question you asked—

19
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,090
I didn't tell the truth.

20
00:02:30,830 --> 00:02:31,850
In '97,

21
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,300
July 2nd,

22
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:36,690
I wasn't home.

23
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,090
That morning, I went to the provincial capital

24
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,650
and bought a Bowls dress.

25
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:44,060
Then

26
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:46,250
I rushed back to Weiyang to return it.

27
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,090
Why did I do that?

28
00:02:49,550 --> 00:02:50,250
To avoid suspicion.

29
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:52,760
To erase the purchase record.

30
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,020
[Buyer: YAO XINCHENG]
Then it can't be traced

31
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,900
back to the dress

32
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,130
at Xu Meng's place.

33
00:02:58,130 --> 00:02:59,670
[Note: New for old, bought in capital, returned in Weiyang.]

34
00:02:59,670 --> 00:03:01,020
If you can't trace Yao Xincheng,

35
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:03,690
then you can't trace me.

36
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:06,220
Qiao Suqing,

37
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,940
too bad you planned it all

38
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:11,300
and still missed one thing.

39
00:03:12,830 --> 00:03:13,900
In your story,

40
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,650
there's a fatal flaw.

41
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:18,740
You said Xu Meng

42
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,090
was killed by Wu Shanlong in '97.

43
00:03:20,430 --> 00:03:21,130
And those shoes,

44
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,570
you got them in 2002.

45
00:03:23,390 --> 00:03:24,940
So why did we find

46
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,130
Xu Meng's DNA

47
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:26,780
in those shoes?

48
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:36,980
[Skin tissue found inside submitted shoes]

49
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:38,270
[STR profile matches Xu Meng's hair sample]

50
00:03:38,270 --> 00:03:38,690
So,

51
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,530
how are you going to explain that?

52
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:47,220
I have no idea.

53
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:49,620
Wu Shanlong is a psycho.

54
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,300
Nothing he does

55
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,300
would surprise me.

56
00:03:53,430 --> 00:03:54,180
Maybe

57
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:58,220
after killing Xu Meng,

58
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,570
he kept her underwear.

59
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,460
Then when he saw

60
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,970
the blue heels on the rack,

61
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:07,300
and

62
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,460
it reminded him of her,

63
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:12,340
so he stuffed the underwear into the shoes.

64
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,530
That's how the skin cells got there.

65
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:17,180
That's possible, right?

66
00:04:25,830 --> 00:04:27,060
Back then, with Uncle Ran,

67
00:04:28,470 --> 00:04:29,450
did you make up the same story?

68
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,620
Ran...

69
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,180
He never doubted me back then.

70
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,730
Nor would he frame me.

71
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,370
Officer He.

72
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,130
At this point,

73
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,060
I admit everything I've done.

74
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,180
But anything I didn't do,

75
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:55,420
I won't admit to any of it.

76
00:04:57,790 --> 00:04:59,100
I've told you everything I should.

77
00:05:00,350 --> 00:05:01,540
If there are more questions,

78
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,740
I won't answer any of them.

79
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:08,370
Qiao Suqing,

80
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:10,540
are you going to resist till the end?

81
00:05:13,390 --> 00:05:14,370
You lied to Uncle Ran,

82
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:15,980
and to me and my dad for years!

83
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,010
Don't you feel

84
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:18,210
any guilt or unease?

85
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:20,890
Officer He.

86
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,250
Ran once said,

87
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:27,810
police rely on evidence.

88
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,940
Otherwise it's all speculation.

89
00:05:36,150 --> 00:05:36,810
Didn't he

90
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:40,370
teach you that?

91
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,500
Uncle He.

92
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:25,570
I'm done.

93
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,980
More and I won't be able to hold it.

94
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,370
Did you find anything?

95
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,250
Right now,

96
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,950
we're running bloodstain tests.

97
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:42,210
Waiting on results.

98
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,420
How about your side?

99
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:47,660
I told you,

100
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:49,980
Qiao Suqing isn't that simple.

101
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,130
This place was wrecked

102
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:54,250
too thoroughly.

103
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:55,010
We can't find

104
00:06:55,030 --> 00:06:56,180
any usable evidence for now.

105
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:58,130
We used luminol on walls and floor,

106
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,940
no positive blood reaction.

107
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,370
Dad,

108
00:07:26,910 --> 00:07:27,450
what do you think about

109
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:28,660
Qiao Suqing confessing

110
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,600
to killing her mother?

111
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,860
She pushed her off a cliff.

112
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:35,300
From what we see,

113
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:37,670
it was hypothermia causing hallucinations

114
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,040
that led to a breakdown.

115
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,100
At most, involuntary manslaughter.

116
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,420
She confessed to this

117
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,540
just to cover up

118
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,660
a bigger crime.

119
00:07:50,590 --> 00:07:51,860
A bigger crime...

120
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:53,690
Eighteen years.

121
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,770
A murderer

122
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,370
never left the scene.

123
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,620
She must have more

124
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,740
secrets to hide.

125
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,100
We don't even have

126
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,250
direct evidence that she killed

127
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,060
Xu Meng and her father.

128
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,210
Other secrets...

129
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:10,500
we can't even start.

130
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,130
Do you think

131
00:08:18,350 --> 00:08:19,860
Uncle Ran found it back then?

132
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:20,940
He must have.

133
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:22,890
Given his personality,

134
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,620
he wouldn't send me

135
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,420
something like that lightly.

136
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,010
He was so meticulous.

137
00:08:29,590 --> 00:08:31,100
He must've kept the evidence

138
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,090
back then.

139
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:33,660
But—

140
00:08:35,830 --> 00:08:37,090
where is it now?

141
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:52,860
[Every event has a center. Beyond it, ripples spread.]

142
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,260
We missed similar cases.

143
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,490
If we take Qiao Suqing

144
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:02,450
as the center,

145
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,060
then the deaths tied to her—

146
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,940
besides Xu Meng and her father,

147
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:07,420
there were "accidental" deaths too.

148
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:09,780
One was Yao Baiyuan in '96.

149
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:10,900
Qian Dajun said

150
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,260
he knocked over a paint bucket,

151
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,300
and fell to his death.

152
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,610
Another was Wu Shanlong in 2002.

153
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,830
He also slipped on oil

154
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:25,850
and fell to his death.

155
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,690
Their deaths are too similar.

156
00:09:29,990 --> 00:09:31,330
Could these not be accidents,

157
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:32,730
but Qiao Suqing

158
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,570
killed them on purpose?

159
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:42,480
Dad,

160
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:43,970
what's wrong?

161
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,780
Your Uncle Ran's accident scene,

162
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,450
there was oil on the ground too.

163
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,040
Qiao?

164
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:46,860
[Mentor]

165
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:50,380
Ran,

166
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:54,270
it's New Year...

167
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:32,780
Qiao Suqing—

168
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:35,540
how could she

169
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,780
do that to Uncle Ran?

170
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:39,900
Back then,

171
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,900
weren't they still...?

172
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:43,730
Unless,

173
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:46,380
she knew Uncle Ran

174
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,210
had found out about her,

175
00:11:47,830 --> 00:11:48,570
and wanted to silence him.

176
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:53,900
If she really did it,

177
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,730
I'll kill her myself.

178
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:04,690
Kiddo,

179
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:06,660
don't rush.

180
00:12:08,590 --> 00:12:10,490
This is just speculation.

181
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,850
We have no proof.

182
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:19,090
Evidence...

183
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:23,740
[Ran Fangxu's Path]

184
00:12:27,350 --> 00:12:28,260
Yao Baiyuan,

185
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:30,300
Wu Shanlong,

186
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:32,570
Ran...

187
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,180
They all

188
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,020
died in "accidents".

189
00:12:39,470 --> 00:12:40,850
These are similar cases.

190
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,780
And at each scene,

191
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,390
there was construction.

192
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,090
On the ground,

193
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:49,210
there was oil residue.

194
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:51,420
That's the killer's method.

195
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,020
Exactly.

196
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,610
Qiao Suqing must've

197
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:57,090
set the trap in advance,

198
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,940
then found ways

199
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:01,300
to lure them in.

200
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:03,660
The parking lot entrance

201
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:05,330
was opened last week!

202
00:13:05,350 --> 00:13:06,490
He might be able to exit from there!

203
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:07,450
Stop!

204
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,380
Move!

205
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,140
[Exit]

206
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:19,060
[Song Qingsong lives in 1703]

207
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:20,780
[Often brings different girls to 1703]

208
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:23,540
Back then,

209
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:26,610
Qiao Suqing deliberately

210
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:27,900
helped us catch Wu Shanlong.

211
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,780
So she could lure him

212
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,140
into the trap she set.

213
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,780
In 2003,

214
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,450
on New Year's Eve...

215
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,450
Qiao.

216
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:44,060
Officer He.

217
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:45,450
Ran

218
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:46,490
didn't come with you?

219
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:47,980
I thought

220
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:48,810
something had come up at work

221
00:13:48,830 --> 00:13:50,780
and kept him busy.

222
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,010
He was supposed to pick me up

223
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:53,820
from work.

224
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,730
I waited,

225
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:55,900
and he never showed.

226
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,260
He didn't answer my calls either.

227
00:13:57,590 --> 00:13:58,980
I was worried you would all be waiting too long,

228
00:13:59,000 --> 00:13:59,930
so

229
00:13:59,950 --> 00:14:01,010
I took a taxi here.

230
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,300
When Qiao Suqing came,

231
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,140
she said herself

232
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:06,610
Uncle Ran would pick her up.

233
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,850
Jiangdong Road was under construction,

234
00:14:10,710 --> 00:14:12,090
and it was on his route.

235
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,610
[Ran Fangxu's Path]
She went ahead

236
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,690
and set it up.

237
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:18,450
She killed Uncle Ran

238
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:21,420
and then came to our place.

239
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,260
Kiddo,

240
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:29,490
Qiao Suqing's detention

241
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:30,690
only lasts 24 hours.

242
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:32,230
Right now,

243
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:34,730
we've got 13 hours left.

244
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,350
Let's cover both sides.

245
00:14:36,630 --> 00:14:37,920
Go find Zhao Jie,

246
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,610
coordinate with traffic police,

247
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,210
get footage from back then

248
00:14:41,230 --> 00:14:42,420
near the crash site.

249
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,090
Check the surveillance.

250
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:45,060
See if Qiao Suqing

251
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,380
was there.

252
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,210
I'll have a good think about

253
00:14:48,710 --> 00:14:49,690
where Ran

254
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,810
might've hidden the evidence.

255
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:57,210
Kiddo!

256
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:01,090
Don't let anger

257
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:01,940
get the best of you.

258
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,490
At this point,

259
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:09,260
this is no longer about solving the case.

260
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,420
This is a showdown

261
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,490
between us and her.

262
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:16,970
Stay calm.

263
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,660
Don't worry.

264
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,420
I'm a cop first and foremost.

265
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,450
Ran...

266
00:15:52,870 --> 00:15:53,940
Where did you

267
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:54,690
put the evidence?

268
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,970
Did Qiao take it?

269
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:03,140
Or was it burned?

270
00:16:30,710 --> 00:16:31,970
It's my fault.

271
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:35,940
All my fault.

272
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,850
I'm the one who

273
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:44,420
put you in danger.

274
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:51,480
Oh, right.

275
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,290
New Year's is next week.

276
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:54,630
On New Year's Eve,

277
00:16:54,990 --> 00:16:55,880
come over for dinner.

278
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:58,090
Bring Qiao too.

279
00:16:58,110 --> 00:16:59,180
We'll all

280
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,730
have a family meal.

281
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:01,450
Don't forget.

282
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,490
It was me who got you killed.

283
00:17:24,840 --> 00:17:25,420
Sir,

284
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,140
if it were you,

285
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,900
how would you keep investigating?

286
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:41,100
[Qian Dajun]

287
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:43,970
Officer Ran,

288
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,820
I saw Ma Qiang's note.

289
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:47,420
What do you need?

290
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:48,660
Manager Qian,

291
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,140
do you know anyone named

292
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,580
YAO XINCHENG in Yuanlongli?

293
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:54,530
Yeah, I know him.

294
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,490
Yao Xincheng.

295
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:57,770
That's him.

296
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:59,250
He kept that woman in 415.

297
00:17:59,990 --> 00:18:00,490
What's her name...

298
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:01,250
Qiao—

299
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:02,660
Qiao Suqing.

300
00:18:12,580 --> 00:18:14,580
[Interrogation Record]

301
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:19,250
Captain Zhao,

302
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:20,730
this is

303
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:21,770
Qian Dajun's interrogation video.

304
00:18:22,990 --> 00:18:24,250
Get Qiao Suqing's too.

305
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:24,940
I want to review everything.

306
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:25,660
Got it.

307
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:29,450
Don't you knock?

308
00:18:31,230 --> 00:18:31,820
What's wrong, Xiaohe?

309
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,010
Wu.

310
00:18:44,470 --> 00:18:46,250
Qu, what a surprise—come sit!

311
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:46,660
No, it's fine.

312
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:47,940
Need a favor.

313
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,730
I need to check all

314
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,450
surveillance from

315
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:51,620
around Jiangdong Road

316
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:52,490
on New Year's Eve 2003.

317
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:54,340
2003?

318
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,340
It's not that I won't help,

319
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,250
citywide traffic footage

320
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:59,820
for one day is massive.

321
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:01,900
We don't even have enough storage for the past year.

322
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:02,900
And you want to check footage

323
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:04,010
from twelve years ago?

324
00:19:04,030 --> 00:19:05,450
- That's impossible... - I don't care!

325
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:06,210
Figure it out!

326
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:07,060
I want it checked!

327
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:09,660
Twelve years ago,

328
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,250
unresolved crash footage,

329
00:19:12,030 --> 00:19:13,660
archives might still have it.

330
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:14,940
Want to dig through it?

331
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:15,820
Yes!

332
00:19:17,270 --> 00:19:17,690
Captain Qu,

333
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,530
on New Year's Eve 2003,

334
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:21,530
heavy rain,

335
00:19:21,710 --> 00:19:22,380
slippery roads,

336
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,370
lots of accidents.

337
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,580
Take your time.

338
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:25,380
I'll be next door.

339
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,000
Call me if needed.

340
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:26,420
Okay.

341
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:26,770
Thanks.

342
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:34,620
Captain Qu,

343
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,210
if Uncle Ran's accident scene

344
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,530
was tampered with by Qiao Suqing beforehand,

345
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:39,380
then start from there

346
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,050
and work outward,

347
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:41,620
check all roads leading in,

348
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,770
then we might find her.

349
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:43,620
Good idea.

350
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:44,860
I'll dig into it.

351
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:45,450
I've got experience.

352
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:46,820
Give me more.

353
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:56,380
Captain Qu,

354
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:58,720
thank you.

355
00:19:59,550 --> 00:20:00,210
No need.

356
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:03,820
Captain Ran wasn't just your uncle,

357
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:05,420
he was my captain

358
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,010
and my partner.

359
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,690
This time, no matter what,

360
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:10,290
we'll find out

361
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:11,180
exactly how he died.

362
00:20:11,990 --> 00:20:12,620
Otherwise,

363
00:20:13,990 --> 00:20:15,660
I don't deserve this badge.

364
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:19,820
Qu,

365
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:22,660
a New Year's gift.

366
00:20:23,510 --> 00:20:24,190
Steep it and drink it.

367
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:25,420
It helps grow hair.

368
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:27,010
Captain,

369
00:20:27,030 --> 00:20:28,380
that's so thoughtful.

370
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:29,290
I—

371
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,100
Happy New Year.

372
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,210
You too.

373
00:20:33,230 --> 00:20:34,250
I'll get going.

374
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:23,860
Ran...

375
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:25,860
Where did you

376
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:26,860
put the evidence?

377
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:28,450
Why do I have

378
00:21:28,470 --> 00:21:29,900
no clue now?

379
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:41,050
Hey,

380
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,050
Mr. He,

381
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,180
are you

382
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:43,730
okay?

383
00:21:45,030 --> 00:21:45,940
I'm fine.

384
00:21:46,470 --> 00:21:48,180
Go handle your work.

385
00:21:48,790 --> 00:21:49,390
Don't worry.

386
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,450
Qu and Xiaohe

387
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:52,860
are checking traffic footage.

388
00:21:53,510 --> 00:21:55,180
I'm reviewing Qiao Suqing's interrogation.

389
00:21:55,470 --> 00:21:56,210
Seeing if

390
00:21:56,230 --> 00:21:57,310
she slipped up anywhere.

391
00:21:58,600 --> 00:21:59,050
By the way,

392
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,450
Ran's belongings—

393
00:22:00,470 --> 00:22:01,530
who sorted them?

394
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:03,250
Could something be missing?

395
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,180
I handled his home myself,

396
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,380
personally.

397
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,250
Nothing should be missing.

398
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:09,940
As for police items,

399
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:10,940
Wang Mangkun sorted them.

400
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,450
Need me to ask him?

401
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:13,610
I can have him call you.

402
00:22:13,790 --> 00:22:14,370
No need.

403
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:16,420
I'll contact him myself.

404
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:17,250
That's it for now.

405
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:20,340
Mr. He...

406
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:21,290
Go on.

407
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,490
You've been through a lot

408
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,100
these past two years.

409
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:29,860
You've

410
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:32,210
stuck with this case,

411
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,490
and his last wish.

412
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:37,530
About this...

413
00:22:40,790 --> 00:22:41,450
I feel guilty.

414
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:44,970
I...

415
00:22:47,470 --> 00:22:48,340
was too late to realize.

416
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:52,580
I failed

417
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,420
as a detective.

418
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:58,860
But don't worry.

419
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:01,940
From now on,

420
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,940
I'll give it everything.

421
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:05,450
I'll do whatever it takes

422
00:23:05,470 --> 00:23:06,180
to find the truth.

423
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,490
I won't let

424
00:23:08,510 --> 00:23:09,620
[Ran Fangxu's Path]
the one who killed him go.

425
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:12,660
Nor will I let him

426
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:15,730
die without answers.

427
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:23,140
You kid,

428
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,140
it's not too late

429
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:26,760
to think like this.

430
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:28,970
Get back to work.

431
00:23:30,230 --> 00:23:30,810
I'm hanging up.

432
00:24:26,270 --> 00:24:26,960
Xiaohe,

433
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,060
take a look.

434
00:24:31,030 --> 00:24:31,920
Can you tell

435
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:32,940
if it's Qiao Suqing?

436
00:24:46,710 --> 00:24:47,340
Don't rush.

437
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:48,820
Let's keep checking outward.

438
00:24:49,470 --> 00:24:50,340
If not at night,

439
00:24:50,550 --> 00:24:51,370
then check daytime.

440
00:24:51,710 --> 00:24:53,140
We'll find her.

441
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:19,220
[Major landslide hit Mount Wu in Kunhai yesterday]

442
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:32,970
Sir,

443
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:33,770
be careful.

444
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,770
Did you forget about your blood pressure?

445
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,530
Ran,

446
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,340
what took you so long?

447
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:41,010
I've got so much to ask.

448
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:42,420
Back then, when you found

449
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,420
Qiao Suqing,

450
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,310
you must've had

451
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,750
solid evidence,

452
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:47,660
right?

453
00:25:52,790 --> 00:25:54,050
Then where did you put it—

454
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:09,360
Sir,

455
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:10,500
what did you say?

456
00:26:10,990 --> 00:26:11,820
I can't hear you.

457
00:26:13,710 --> 00:26:14,420
I said,

458
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:16,580
the evidence you used

459
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:17,580
to identify Qiao Suqing—

460
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,770
where is it?

461
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:27,930
What did you say?

462
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:30,100
Hold on!

463
00:26:36,070 --> 00:26:36,860
Go ahead!

464
00:26:40,030 --> 00:26:40,660
Oh.

465
00:26:50,030 --> 00:26:50,490
You—

466
00:26:50,510 --> 00:26:51,740
Don't worry about me!

467
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:54,340
I'm doing fine!

468
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,580
Xiaohe's fine too!

469
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,820
Zhao Jie's fine!

470
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:00,660
We're all doing well!

471
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,900
So don't worry!

472
00:27:15,070 --> 00:27:15,730
Ran...

473
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:22,820
Ran...

474
00:27:24,790 --> 00:27:25,420
Ran...

475
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:28,900
Ran...

476
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:11,700
[ICU Family Visiting Room]

477
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:13,260
Doctor,

478
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:14,590
how's my dad?

479
00:28:14,750 --> 00:28:15,680
Which one is your dad?

480
00:28:16,470 --> 00:28:16,900
This one.

481
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:18,340
Don't worry.

482
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:19,280
He's not in danger.

483
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:20,010
But,

484
00:28:20,030 --> 00:28:21,210
he has weak vessels,

485
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,690
overworked lately,

486
00:28:22,710 --> 00:28:24,660
and missed his meds,

487
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:25,450
triggering

488
00:28:25,470 --> 00:28:26,660
an ischemic stroke.

489
00:28:26,990 --> 00:28:27,530
He needs

490
00:28:27,550 --> 00:28:28,450
to stay for observation.

491
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:30,010
Thank you, doctor.

492
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:30,730
You're welcome.

493
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,010
Manager Ma, thank you.

494
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:34,860
It's nothing, really.

495
00:28:35,230 --> 00:28:36,730
It's our job.

496
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,730
As long as Yuanlongli stands,

497
00:28:38,750 --> 00:28:39,820
I'll do my duty

498
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:41,100
as property manager.

499
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:42,420
By the way,

500
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:45,420
this was in Mr. He's hand

501
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,530
when he collapsed.

502
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:47,530
It took effort

503
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:48,380
to pry it out.

504
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,620
I'll head back first.

505
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:51,690
If you need anything,

506
00:28:51,710 --> 00:28:52,490
just call me.

507
00:28:53,070 --> 00:28:53,660
Thanks.

508
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:54,640
No problem.

509
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:08,140
What happened?

510
00:29:08,510 --> 00:29:09,770
I was on the phone with him,

511
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:10,660
and he suddenly fainted?

512
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:11,780
Doctor said it's nothing serious,

513
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:12,820
just overwork

514
00:29:12,840 --> 00:29:13,770
triggering his condition.

515
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:16,380
That's a relief.

516
00:29:17,510 --> 00:29:18,100
How about this—

517
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,380
work can wait.

518
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,450
Put it aside.

519
00:29:20,470 --> 00:29:21,580
Stay and take care of him.

520
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:22,380
Captain—

521
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:23,970
My dad's

522
00:29:23,990 --> 00:29:25,340
in there,

523
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,290
and I can't help much.

524
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:28,420
I'd rather work the case

525
00:29:28,440 --> 00:29:29,490
and find the truth.

526
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:34,690
The June 30 case is reopened.

527
00:29:35,270 --> 00:29:36,660
Xiaohe should lead it.

528
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:38,490
The team and I

529
00:29:38,990 --> 00:29:39,820
will back her up.

530
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:41,380
And besides,

531
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:42,100
solving it

532
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,820
isn't just Ran's wish,

533
00:29:44,710 --> 00:29:45,900
it's He Yuanhang's too.

534
00:29:54,510 --> 00:29:54,820
Alright.

535
00:29:55,790 --> 00:29:56,860
Talk to the doctor,

536
00:29:57,230 --> 00:29:57,940
then get back ASAP.

537
00:29:58,360 --> 00:29:59,140
Thank you, Captain.

538
00:30:04,990 --> 00:30:05,660
Before I came,

539
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,970
I found another clip.

540
00:30:06,990 --> 00:30:08,210
Same woman with the umbrella.

541
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:09,580
I copied it for you.

542
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:11,660
Two drives left to check.

543
00:30:12,030 --> 00:30:13,290
I'll head back and continue.

544
00:30:13,710 --> 00:30:14,100
Captain Qu!

545
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:17,340
Thank you.

546
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:20,770
What's with you?

547
00:30:21,270 --> 00:30:22,530
Thanking me twice today.

548
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,490
Last time

549
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,290
it was for my uncle.

550
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:28,580
This time,

551
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,210
it's for my dad.

552
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:40,050
The two of us

553
00:30:40,710 --> 00:30:41,730
worked together for years.

554
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,530
Seeing him now,

555
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:46,450
lying there

556
00:30:46,470 --> 00:30:47,180
against his will—

557
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:50,290
it just

558
00:30:52,070 --> 00:30:53,010
doesn't feel good.

559
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:02,860
When he's better,

560
00:31:03,510 --> 00:31:04,180
tell him

561
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:05,940
he owes me one.

562
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:07,900
I'm off.

563
00:31:10,470 --> 00:31:10,940
Captain Qu!

564
00:31:43,310 --> 00:31:44,420
This whole story

565
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,100
you've been plotting it

566
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:47,530
for years, haven't you?

567
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:49,970
Xiaohe,

568
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:56,580
I even admitted I pushed my own mother

569
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,010
off a cliff by accident.

570
00:31:58,030 --> 00:31:59,290
I told you that myself.

571
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:00,730
So making up anything else,

572
00:32:00,750 --> 00:32:01,900
what would be the point?

573
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:17,900
Captain,

574
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:18,820
reporting in.

575
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,970
Qiao Suqing is assisting now.

576
00:32:20,990 --> 00:32:22,530
If we can't detain her,

577
00:32:22,550 --> 00:32:23,290
in three hours,

578
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:24,340
the hold expires.

579
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:25,860
Then

580
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:26,940
we'll have to release her?

581
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:28,420
Why so eager?

582
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,420
We've got three hours.

583
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:30,180
Get out!

584
00:32:30,710 --> 00:32:31,290
Don't bother me!

585
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:55,340
Qu said

586
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:56,860
you made some progress with the surveillance—

587
00:32:57,470 --> 00:32:58,420
why are you just sitting here?

588
00:32:59,230 --> 00:33:00,010
The footage,

589
00:33:00,030 --> 00:33:00,860
it's just a lead.

590
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:03,100
We still lack proof.

591
00:33:04,990 --> 00:33:06,010
This note my dad wrote

592
00:33:06,030 --> 00:33:07,250
before he collapsed—

593
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:08,660
I keep thinking,

594
00:33:08,990 --> 00:33:10,530
could it be linked to what

595
00:33:10,550 --> 00:33:11,580
Uncle Ran found?

596
00:33:18,710 --> 00:33:19,900
Captain Zhao said

597
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,530
before Mr. He collapsed,

598
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,380
he asked

599
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,140
about Ran's belongings.

600
00:33:25,710 --> 00:33:27,050
Back then,

601
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:27,970
I handled that.

602
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,730
I even went back

603
00:33:29,750 --> 00:33:30,380
and checked again.

604
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:32,660
It was all routine files.

605
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,490
Whether

606
00:33:33,510 --> 00:33:34,970
paper

607
00:33:34,990 --> 00:33:35,940
or digital,

608
00:33:36,750 --> 00:33:37,820
nothing stood out.

609
00:33:43,030 --> 00:33:43,940
Digital...

610
00:33:46,310 --> 00:33:47,050
the office system?

611
00:33:47,750 --> 00:33:48,450
No way.

612
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:50,420
I took over his account

613
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:52,290
and internal email.

614
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:54,210
Nothing unusual.

615
00:33:55,070 --> 00:33:56,620
I remember that morning,

616
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:58,450
he rushed back

617
00:33:58,470 --> 00:33:59,450
didn't even greet anyone,

618
00:33:59,470 --> 00:34:00,660
and went straight into his office.

619
00:34:00,990 --> 00:34:01,580
Wait—

620
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:02,180
I remember.

621
00:34:02,510 --> 00:34:03,940
I went in that day.

622
00:34:04,510 --> 00:34:05,290
It's New Year—

623
00:34:05,310 --> 00:34:05,970
why are you still busy?

624
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:07,340
Nothing.

625
00:34:08,470 --> 00:34:10,380
Writing a case summary email.

626
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:11,420
What case?

627
00:34:11,630 --> 00:34:12,420
I never heard of it.

628
00:34:14,990 --> 00:34:15,820
He was at his desk,

629
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:17,010
said he was writing

630
00:34:17,030 --> 00:34:19,260
a case summary email.

631
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:20,500
That day,

632
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,340
did any of you get his email?

633
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:27,780
Could it be

634
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,650
an internal email to my dad?

635
00:34:29,670 --> 00:34:30,220
No.

636
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:31,650
Back then,

637
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:32,650
he never used computers.

638
00:34:33,030 --> 00:34:33,570
His

639
00:34:33,590 --> 00:34:34,570
system account

640
00:34:34,590 --> 00:34:35,490
and internal email...

641
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:36,420
he never

642
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:37,170
used them.

643
00:34:38,150 --> 00:34:39,530
But the system account

644
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:40,780
is just full-name pinyin.

645
00:34:42,160 --> 00:34:42,670
Wait,

646
00:34:43,030 --> 00:34:44,570
you handle retired accounts,

647
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:45,300
right?

648
00:34:45,990 --> 00:34:46,440
Captain,

649
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,880
I actually came across

650
00:34:49,190 --> 00:34:50,620
Mr. He's account while

651
00:34:51,120 --> 00:34:52,220
organizing the system.

652
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,090
What are you waiting for?

653
00:34:53,090 --> 00:34:54,210
Log in, now.

654
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,630
After I saw it,

655
00:34:57,060 --> 00:34:58,650
I deleted it.

656
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:00,860
Why so eager?

657
00:35:09,710 --> 00:35:10,440
Liu,

658
00:35:11,110 --> 00:35:12,300
can you restore

659
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,120
a deleted account?

660
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,610
A deleted account,

661
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:16,320
if it needs recovery,

662
00:35:16,470 --> 00:35:17,220
we'd have to send the main drive

663
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,840
to the city IT center.

664
00:35:18,990 --> 00:35:19,650
That won't work.

665
00:35:19,670 --> 00:35:20,630
How long would that take?

666
00:35:20,630 --> 00:35:21,490
I need it now.

667
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:22,450
Captain,

668
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:23,650
that's beyond us.

669
00:35:24,150 --> 00:35:25,420
We're cops,

670
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,220
not hackers.

671
00:35:31,990 --> 00:35:32,530
Hackers.

672
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:35,940
Check up and down,

673
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,130
left and right—

674
00:35:37,990 --> 00:35:38,740
He's a hacker.

675
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:40,170
A hacker?

676
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:42,570
I'm not a hacker.

677
00:35:42,590 --> 00:35:43,490
You got the wrong guy.

678
00:35:43,510 --> 00:35:44,650
I'm innocent.

679
00:35:44,670 --> 00:35:45,680
Take him first!

680
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:46,740
Move!

681
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:47,400
- Wait... - Come on.

682
00:35:48,270 --> 00:35:49,330
Where? My computer—

683
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:50,470
Where are we going?

684
00:36:09,510 --> 00:36:10,300
Relax.

685
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,220
We just need help on data recovery.

686
00:36:12,220 --> 00:36:13,260
It's approved.

687
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:14,980
Handled technically.

688
00:36:15,070 --> 00:36:15,970
It's all legal,

689
00:36:15,990 --> 00:36:17,000
and secure.

690
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,130
Make way!

691
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:20,610
Here's fuel for him.

692
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:21,260
Here.

693
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:22,260
Drink up.

694
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,340
The system's

695
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,260
hard drive—

696
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,130
ever replaced?

697
00:36:43,150 --> 00:36:43,610
No.

698
00:36:45,110 --> 00:36:46,010
Five minutes.

699
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:22,060
[Enter Password]

700
00:37:25,110 --> 00:37:26,650
The data's still there.

701
00:37:27,470 --> 00:37:28,530
It's encrypted.

702
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:30,650
If you don't know the password,

703
00:37:30,670 --> 00:37:32,220
I can install a hacking tool

704
00:37:32,740 --> 00:37:33,520
and crack it.

705
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:34,450
Are you crazy?

706
00:37:34,470 --> 00:37:36,010
Installing random software

707
00:37:36,030 --> 00:37:36,970
on police computers?

708
00:37:36,990 --> 00:37:37,860
You want jail time?

709
00:37:44,150 --> 00:37:44,780
I'll try.

710
00:37:54,020 --> 00:37:55,900
[Enter Password]

711
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:56,500
[ERROR]

712
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:00,940
I'll try a birthday.

713
00:38:01,300 --> 00:38:07,140
[Enter Password]

714
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:07,940
[ERROR]

715
00:38:13,170 --> 00:38:13,840
Wait!

716
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:16,000
Last try.

717
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:17,390
One more and it locks.

718
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:37,970
Your teacher said

719
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,700
you ranked

720
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,050
last in finals.

721
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:46,900
Last place is fine.

722
00:38:47,630 --> 00:38:48,340
Not so bad.

723
00:38:51,110 --> 00:38:52,130
Last place

724
00:38:52,150 --> 00:38:52,820
and still fine?

725
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:54,530
Tell me—

726
00:38:55,550 --> 00:38:57,050
If someone stands on Earth

727
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:58,860
and keeps walking south,

728
00:38:59,630 --> 00:39:00,260
where do they end up?

729
00:39:02,510 --> 00:39:03,820
Keep going south...

730
00:39:05,470 --> 00:39:06,380
as far south as possible.

731
00:39:11,110 --> 00:39:12,530
You'll reach

732
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:13,420
the South Pole.

733
00:39:14,190 --> 00:39:15,860
But once you're there,

734
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,780
any direction you go

735
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,260
won't be south anymore.

736
00:39:21,110 --> 00:39:21,650
Xiaohe,

737
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,970
we're both at the bottom.

738
00:39:25,190 --> 00:39:27,260
Your birthday's March 31.

739
00:39:28,030 --> 00:39:29,050
Mine's

740
00:39:29,070 --> 00:39:30,170
June 30.

741
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:32,380
Last day of the month.

742
00:39:33,150 --> 00:39:34,300
But think of it—

743
00:39:35,470 --> 00:39:36,420
the next day

744
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:37,380
after our birthdays

745
00:39:38,070 --> 00:39:38,700
is always

746
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:39,530
a new month.

747
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:42,090
I like that.

748
00:39:50,630 --> 00:39:51,740
It's my dad's account.

749
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,570
Uncle Ran wouldn't

750
00:39:53,590 --> 00:39:54,900
use his own birthday.

751
00:40:00,060 --> 00:40:02,900
[Enter Password]

752
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:07,140
[Good evening, He Yuanhang]

753
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:09,220
Got it!

754
00:40:15,460 --> 00:40:17,540
[Inbox: 0 unread]

755
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:20,530
There's nothing.

756
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:23,010
Check drafts.

757
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:26,980
[Drafts]

758
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:27,980
[June 30 Case Reinvestigation Report]

759
00:40:33,110 --> 00:40:33,900
Dear leaders,

760
00:40:34,630 --> 00:40:35,420
colleagues,

761
00:40:35,990 --> 00:40:36,970
this is He Yuanhang.

762
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:38,820
As a recognized contributor

763
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:39,650
to the June 30 case,

764
00:40:40,470 --> 00:40:41,130
I have a duty

765
00:40:41,630 --> 00:40:43,610
to report the findings of

766
00:40:44,190 --> 00:40:45,380
the reinvestigation as follows...

767
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,260
He already wrote a report,

768
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,340
why keep investigating?

769
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:53,420
He lost his memory.

770
00:40:55,070 --> 00:40:55,650
What do you know?

771
00:40:56,240 --> 00:40:57,420
This must have been written by Captain Ran.

772
00:40:57,840 --> 00:40:58,530
He didn't want to affect

773
00:40:58,550 --> 00:40:59,650
He Yuanhang's merit award,

774
00:41:00,070 --> 00:41:00,700
so

775
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:01,820
he put the credit

776
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:02,740
on He Yuanhang.

777
00:41:04,620 --> 00:41:09,180
[June 30 Evidence]

778
00:41:10,460 --> 00:41:11,260
[June 30 Evidence]

779
00:41:11,300 --> 00:41:13,260
[Evidence List, Evidence Locations]

780
00:41:13,260 --> 00:41:15,340
[Evidence List]

781
00:41:26,580 --> 00:41:28,220
[Evidence Locations]

782
00:41:35,470 --> 00:41:36,340
Captain Ran's toolbox.

783
00:41:38,590 --> 00:41:39,170
It's at my place.

784
00:42:09,550 --> 00:42:10,130
Officer Ran,

785
00:42:11,550 --> 00:42:12,420
what are you doing here?

786
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:28,860
Who are you looking for?

787
00:42:35,990 --> 00:42:36,860
Can we talk inside?

788
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:45,820
♪I hear a voice from the depths of the valley♪

789
00:42:46,820 --> 00:42:50,180
♪Tinged with madness♪

790
00:42:50,700 --> 00:42:54,020
♪And hysteria♪

791
00:42:55,940 --> 00:43:00,660
♪I see the familiar self in my dream♪

792
00:43:02,260 --> 00:43:05,620
♪So avoidant♪

793
00:43:06,140 --> 00:43:09,460
♪So distraught♪

794
00:43:11,100 --> 00:43:15,820
♪That was a faraway memory♪

795
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:20,780
♪I'm praying♪

796
00:43:21,260 --> 00:43:24,620
♪For my fate♪

797
00:43:26,900 --> 00:43:31,540
♪That's a secret that only belongs to time♪

798
00:43:32,780 --> 00:43:36,140
♪It's only a secret♪

799
00:43:36,620 --> 00:43:39,980
♪If no one brings it up♪

800
00:43:41,220 --> 00:43:44,740
♪Who will complete the puzzle of this lie♪

801
00:43:45,180 --> 00:43:48,900
♪Line by line, whose name are they calling out?♪

802
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:52,700
♪Nightfall is the finale of all answers♪

803
00:43:52,700 --> 00:43:56,380
♪Only belonging to this barren land♪

804
00:43:56,460 --> 00:44:00,340
♪Who came from the forsaken crowd?♪

805
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:04,380
♪Caressing a rusted body♪

806
00:44:04,380 --> 00:44:08,220
♪Stashing the secret on a certain floor♪

807
00:44:08,220 --> 00:44:16,060
♪Without making any ripples♪

808
00:44:18,900 --> 00:44:24,540
♪Any ripples♪

809
00:44:25,020 --> 00:44:28,540
♪Who will complete the puzzle of this lie♪

810
00:44:29,020 --> 00:44:32,700
♪Line by line, whose name are they calling out?♪

811
00:44:32,780 --> 00:44:36,460
♪Nightfall is the finale of all answers♪

812
00:44:36,460 --> 00:44:40,180
♪Only belonging to this barren land♪

813
00:44:40,220 --> 00:44:44,140
♪Who came from the forsaken crowd?♪

814
00:44:44,300 --> 00:44:48,180
♪Caressing a rusted body♪

815
00:44:48,180 --> 00:44:52,020
♪Stashing the secret on a certain floor♪

816
00:44:52,020 --> 00:45:02,660
♪In the loneliness of nightfall♪
